= First Independence Congress

With meticoulous planning various representatives from across the Sahellan political spectrum have arrived for the First Independence Congress. There is palpable excitement and nervousness amongst the delegates gathered as to who will be appointed to which ministries. Especially important at the congress are the three largest political parties, the National Emancipation Front, Alliance for Freedom and Popular Stability however there are also a range of important cultural, intellectual and financial figures not tied to any of the parties. 

